The paper deals with complexity issues related to Boolean satisfiability problems, which are central to computational complexity theory. The paper also discusses connectivity properties of the solution graph, which is a graph-theoretic representation of the solution space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
